HEADWORD: Fourdrinier
<hw>Four`dri`nier"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A machine used
in making paper; -- so named from an early inventor of improvements in
this class of machinery.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fourfold</ent>⟦br⟧
